  "title": "use-consistent-global-store-name",
  "contents": "\n\n\n  <div class=\"github-links\">\n    <a href=\"https://github.com/ngrx/platform/edit/main/projects/ngrx.io/content/guide/eslint-plugin/rules/use-consistent-global-store-name.md?message=docs%3A%20describe%20your%20change...\" aria-label=\"Suggest Edits\" title=\"Suggest Edits\"><i class=\"material-icons\" aria-hidden=\"true\" role=\"img\">mode_edit</i></a>\n  </div>\n\n\n<div class=\"content\">\n<h1 id=\"use-consistent-global-store-name\">use-consistent-global-store-name<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/eslint-plugin/rules/use-consistent-global-store-name#use-consistent-global-store-name\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h1>\n<p>Use a consistent name for the global store.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Type</strong>: suggestion</li>\n<li><strong>Fixable</strong>: No</li>\n<li><strong>Suggestion</strong>: Yes</li>\n<li><strong>Requires type checking</strong>: No</li>\n<li><strong>Configurable</strong>: Yes</li>\n</ul>\n<!-- Everything above this generated, do not edit -->\n<!-- MANUAL-DOC:START -->\n<h2 id=\"rule-details\">Rule Details<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/eslint-plugin/rules/use-consistent-global-store-name#rule-details\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n<p>The name of the global store should be used consistent.</p>\n<p>Examples of <strong>incorrect</strong> code for this rule:</p>\n<code-example language=\"ts\">\n<a href=\"api/store-devtools/DevToolsFeatureOptions#export\" class=\"code-anchor\">export</a> class ClassOne {\n  constructor(private store: <a href=\"api/store/Store\" class=\"code-anchor\">Store</a>) {}\n}\n\n<a href=\"api/store-devtools/DevToolsFeatureOptions#export\" class=\"code-anchor\">export</a> class ClassTwo {\n  constructor(private customersStore: <a href=\"api/store/Store\" class=\"code-anchor\">Store</a>) {}\n}\n</code-example>\n<p>Examples of <strong>correct</strong> code for this rule:</p>\n<code-example language=\"ts\">\n<a href=\"api/store-devtools/DevToolsFeatureOptions#export\" class=\"code-anchor\">export</a> class ClassOne {\n  constructor(private store: <a href=\"api/store/Store\" class=\"code-anchor\">Store</a>) {}\n}\n\n<a href=\"api/store-devtools/DevToolsFeatureOptions#export\" class=\"code-anchor\">export</a> class ClassTwo {\n  constructor(private store: <a href=\"api/store/Store\" class=\"code-anchor\">Store</a>) {}\n}\n</code-example>\n<h2 id=\"rule-config\">Rule Config<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"guide/eslint-plugin/rules/use-consistent-global-store-name#rule-config\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n<p>To configure this rule you can change the preferred <code>name</code> of the global store.\nThe default is <code>store</code>.</p>\n<p>To change the name of the global store use:</p>\n<code-example language=\"json\">\n\"rules\": {\n  \"@ngrx/use-consistent-global-store-name\": [\"warn\", \"store$\"]\n}\n</code-example>\n\n</div>\n\n<!-- links to this doc:\n-->\n<!-- links from this doc:\n - api/store-devtools/DevToolsFeatureOptions#export\n - api/store/Store\n - guide/eslint-plugin/rules/use-consistent-global-store-name#rule-config\n - guide/eslint-plugin/rules/use-consistent-global-store-name#rule-details\n - guide/eslint-plugin/rules/use-consistent-global-store-name#use-consistent-global-store-name\n - https://github.com/ngrx/platform/edit/main/projects/ngrx.io/content/guide/eslint-plugin/rules/use-consistent-global-store-name.md?message=docs%3A%20describe%20your%20change...\n-->"
}